documentation.value:
A Caddyfile site block with an address.

```caddyfile
example.com {
    # directives
}
```

A site block listening on a specific port.

```caddyfile
:8080 {
    respond "Hello"
}
```

Match all subdomains with a wildcard.

```caddyfile
*.example.com {
    tls {
        dns cloudflare {env.CF_API_TOKEN}
    }
}
```

Serve multiple domains from one block.

```caddyfile
example.com www.example.com {
    respond "Hello"
}
```

Explicit HTTPS site block.

```caddyfile
https://example.com {
    respond "Secure!"
}
```

Serve over plain HTTP (no automatic HTTPS).

```caddyfile
http://example.com {
    respond "Not encrypted"
}
```

Proxy with custom header modifications.

```caddyfile
reverse_proxy localhost:3000 {
    header_up Host {upstream_hostport}
    header_up X-Real-IP {remote_host}
}
```

Load balance across multiple backends.

```caddyfile
reverse_proxy localhost:3001 localhost:3002 localhost:3003 {
    lb_policy round_robin
}
```

Configure the upstream transport (e.g., for HTTPS backends).

```caddyfile
reverse_proxy localhost:8443 {
    transport http {
        tls_insecure_skip_verify
    }
}
```

Hide certain files from being served.

```caddyfile
file_server {
    hide .git .env
}
```

Static response with headers.

```caddyfile
respond "OK" 200 {
    header Content-Type text/plain
}
```

Protect a site with HTTP Basic Auth.

```caddyfile
basicauth /admin/* {
    admin $2a$14$hash...
}
```

Enable and configure request logging.

```caddyfile
log {
    output file /var/log/caddy/access.log
}
```

Write logs to a file.

```caddyfile
log {
    output file /var/log/caddy/access.log {
        roll_size 100mb
        roll_keep 5
    }
}
```

Use a custom log format.

```caddyfile
log {
    format json
}
```

Sample logs to reduce volume.

```caddyfile
log {
    sampling {
        interval 100
        first 10
        thereafter 20
    }
}
```

Use Caddy's internal issuer.

```caddyfile
tls internal {
    on_demand
}
```

Use DNS challenge for wildcard or non-public certs.

```caddyfile
tls {
    dns cloudflare {env.CF_API_TOKEN}
}
```

Restrict TLS protocol versions.

```caddyfile
tls {
    protocols tls1.2 tls1.3
}
```

Specify allowed cipher suites.

```caddyfile
tls {
    ciphers TLS_AES_256_GCM_SHA384 TLS_CHACHA20_POLY1305_SHA256
}
```

Require client certificates.

```caddyfile
tls {
    client_auth {
        mode require_and_verify
        trusted_ca_cert_file /etc/caddy/ca.pem
    }
}
```

Mutually exclusive handler groups. First matching block wins.

```caddyfile
handle /api/* {
    reverse_proxy localhost:8080
}
```

Like handle, but strips the matched path prefix before handling.

```caddyfile
handle_path /api/* {
    reverse_proxy localhost:8080
}
```

PHP FastCGI with custom split path info.

```caddyfile
php_fastcgi localhost:9000 {
    split .php
}
```

Define custom error pages.

```caddyfile
handle_errors {
    respond "{err.status_code} {err.status_text}"
}
```

Custom error page with status code.

```caddyfile
handle_errors {
    @404 expression {err.status_code} == 404
    handle @404 {
        rewrite * /404.html
        file_server
    }
}
```

Map variables for later use in the request context.

```caddyfile
vars {
    my_var "some value"
}
```

Enable distributed tracing (OpenTelemetry).

```caddyfile
tracing {
    span my-span
}
```

Match based on file existence.

```caddyfile
@static file {
    try_files {path} {path}/index.html
}
```

Named matcher for API routes.

```caddyfile
@api {
    path /api/*
}
```

Named matcher for static assets.

```caddyfile
@static {
    path *.css *.js *.png *.jpg *.gif *.svg *.ico *.woff *.woff2
}
```

Named matcher for WebSocket upgrades.

```caddyfile
@websocket {
    header Connection *Upgrade*
    header Upgrade websocket
}
```

Email for ACME certificate registration.

```caddyfile
{
    email admin@example.com
}
```

Custom ACME Certificate Authority endpoint.

```caddyfile
{
    acme_ca https://acme-staging-v02.api.letsencrypt.org/directory
}
```

Configure DNS challenge provider globally.

```caddyfile
{
    acme_dns cloudflare {env.CF_API_TOKEN}
}
```

Configure the admin API endpoint.

```caddyfile
{
    admin off
}
```

Control automatic HTTPS behavior.

```caddyfile
{
    auto_https off
}
```

Set the shutdown grace period.

```caddyfile
{
    grace_period 30s
}
```

Configure listener servers.

```caddyfile
{
    servers {
        protocol {
            experimental_http3
        }
    }
}
```

Configure global (non-site) logging.

```caddyfile
{
    log {
        level INFO
        output stderr
    }
}
```

Control OCSP stapling behavior.

```caddyfile
{
    ocsp_stapling off
}
```

Configure TLS certificate storage backend.

```caddyfile
{
    storage file_system {
        root /data/caddy
    }
}
```

Change the evaluation order of directives.

```caddyfile
{
    order my_directive before respond
}
```

Use locally-trusted certificates.

```caddyfile
{
    local_certs
}
```

Skip installing root CA in the system trust store.

```caddyfile
{
    skip_install_trust
}
```

Full SPA with reverse proxy for API.

```caddyfile
example.com {
    handle /api/* {
        reverse_proxy localhost:3000
    }
    handle {
        root * /var/www/spa
        try_files {path} /index.html
        file_server
    }
}
```

completions.insertText:
${1:example.com} {
	handle /api/* {
		reverse_proxy ${2:localhost:3000}
	}
	handle {
		root * ${3:/var/www/spa}
		try_files {path} /index.html
		file_server
	}
}

