documentation.value:
Load balance across multiple backends.

```caddyfile
example.com {
    reverse_proxy localhost:3001 localhost:3002 localhost:3003 {
        lb_policy round_robin
        health_uri /health
        health_interval 10s
    }
}
```

Wildcard certificate with DNS challenge.

```caddyfile
*.example.com {
    tls {
        dns cloudflare {env.CF_API_TOKEN}
    }
    @app1 host app1.example.com
    handle @app1 {
        reverse_proxy localhost:3001
    }
}
```

Force all traffic to HTTPS (Caddy does this automatically, but explicit version).

```caddyfile
http://example.com {
    redir https://{host}{uri} permanent
}
```

Serve multiple sites from one Caddyfile.

```caddyfile
site1.example.com {
    root * /var/www/site1
    file_server
}

site2.example.com {
    reverse_proxy localhost:3000
}
```

Proxy gRPC traffic.

```caddyfile
grpc.example.com {
    reverse_proxy h2c://localhost:50051
}
```

Proxy WebSocket connections.

```caddyfile
example.com {
    @websocket {
        header Connection *Upgrade*
        header Upgrade websocket
    }
    reverse_proxy @websocket localhost:8080
    reverse_proxy localhost:3000
}
```

completions.insertText:
${1:example.com} {
	@websocket {
		header Connection *Upgrade*
		header Upgrade websocket
	}
	reverse_proxy @websocket ${2:localhost:8080}
	reverse_proxy ${3:localhost:3000}
}

